parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To go away, depart, begone, die. From hupo and ago; to lead under, i.e. Withdraw or retire, literally or figuratively.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A village, country town. From keimai; a hamlet.
Opposite, in front (of), over against. From kata and enanti; directly opposite.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To journey in(to), I go in(to), enter, intervene. From eis and poreuomai; to enter.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.
A colt, young ass, foal. Apparently a primary word; a 'foal' or 'filly', i.e., a young ass.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Middle or Passive - Accusative Masculine Singular
str2: To bind, tie, fasten; I impel, compel; I declare to be prohibited and unlawful. A primary verb; to bind.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Accusative Masculine Singular

str2: At any time, ever. From po and pote; at any time, i.e. at no time.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Another form for kathezomai; to seat down, i.e. Set; intransitively, to sit; figuratively, to settle.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

str2: A primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, go, pass, or induce.
